The Void Citadel is Kel'Shadra's recurrence engine: a high-command complex where testimony was iterated until it produced politically acceptable outcomes.

Early Kel'Shadra doctrine treated memory as sacred evidence. That failed when power learned to weaponize archival latency.
The Citadel industrialized the loophole. Three formalized processes:
  Extraction - isolate testimony from its witness context.
  Projection - reframe testimony into sanctioned doctrinal syntax.
  Recurrence - replay unresolved testimony cycles until resistance decays.

Built around a vertical paradox. The Null Spire above concentrates void pressure and symbolic authority.
Catacomb compression halls below compact bodies, records, and legal identities into tractable units.

Four offices governed the apparatus:
  Recurrence Chancery - determined which cases were "incomplete" using criteria a witness could never satisfy.
  Null Spire Conductorate - tuned void harmonics to disorient detainees.
  Heraldic Ten - staged concurrence so each member could claim constrained responsibility.
  Annex Scribes - demoted dissidents who inadvertently preserved unredacted counter-histories.

Under Velastra, the Citadel created bifurcated truth: fast truth for approved factions, perpetual review for everyone else.
